  "text": "Experiment 1 demonstrated that only a handful of steps are needed by cochlear implant listeners for consonant identification under quiet conditions. However, under more realistic conditions w ith background noise, a greater number of steps might be needed. [CITATION_1] noted that although the dynamic range reduction degraded phoneme recognition in quiet marginally, it had a significant effect in noise. Similarly, Wilson and colleagues (unpublished) noted that more steps were required t o reach asymptotic performance in noise. More studies are needed to investigate the effect of number of steps on speech understanding under noisy conditions.",
